<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1023291-i-didn-t-get-many-of-the-color-names-why">I didn&#39;t get many of the color names. Why are &quot;Lincoln&quot; and &quot;Brunswick&quot; associated with green, for example?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1023291'><a id="like_count_community_question_1023291" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1023291?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F2113260.Shades_of_Grey">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1023291-i-didn-t-get-many-of-the-color-names-why">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1023291-i-didn-t-get-many-of-the-color-names-why">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/96556805-johno"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/96556805-johno">JohnO</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The town of Lincoln in England produced cloth in medieval times and their green dye was famous for its colour. They used Woad to make a blue then adde<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The town of Lincoln in England produced cloth in medieval times and their green dye was famous for its colour. They used Woad to make a blue then added another plant-based yellow dye as a secondary, to produce their green. Other towns were known for other colours. Brunswick green seems to have originated in Germany, in Braunschweig, which became Brunswick in English.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

